# UiPath Agent Skills

This repository contains domain knowledge packages (skills) for building, running, testing, and deploying UiPath automations and agents.

## Repository Structure

- `skills/` — All skills, each in its own directory with a `SKILL.md` and optional `references/`, `assets/`, `scripts/` subdirectories
- `skills-community/` — Community-built skills, reviewed by UiPath
- `skills-experimental/` — Experimental skills under active development. Always confirm with the user before using.
- `references/activity-docs/` — UiPath activity package documentation
- `hooks/` — Session hooks (ensure-uip.sh)
- `.claude-plugin/` — Claude Code plugin + marketplace registration
- `.agents/` — Codex CLI skill discovery (symlinks to `skills/`)
- `.codex/` — Codex CLI project configuration
- `.cursor/rules/` — Cursor IDE project rules

## Skills

### Core Skills (in `skills/`)
- **uipath-coded-workflows** — C# coded automation creation, editing, building, and running
- **uipath-rpa-workflows** — XAML RPA workflow generation and editing
- **uipath-flow** — JSON-based Flow project creation and debugging
- **uipath-platform** — Authentication, Orchestrator, deployment, CLI tools
- **uipath-servo** — Desktop and browser UI automation and testing

### Experimental Skills (in `skills-experimental/`)
- **uipath-coded-agents** — End-to-end toolkit for coded agents (scaffold, build, run, evaluate, deploy, sync)

## Skill Format

Each skill directory contains:
- `SKILL.md` — YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`) + markdown instructions
- `references/` — Domain documentation and guides
- `assets/` — Templates and resources
- `scripts/` — Automation scripts

## Conventions

- Skills use YAML frontmatter with `name` and `description` fields
- The `description` field explains when the skill should and should not trigger
- Reference docs are markdown files organized by domain area
- Experimental skills require explicit user confirmation before use
